Document: ENetMultiplayerPeer
Path: godot/classes/class_enetmultiplayerpeer.rst
Summary: Provides ENet-based network functionality for multiplayer games.

ENetMultiplayerPeer is a high-level multiplayer API that uses the ENet library for reliable UDP communication. It allows you to create peer-to-peer or client-server connections for multiplayer games.

Inherits: MultiplayerPeer < RefCounted

This class provides methods for managing network connections, sending and receiving data, and handling player management. It's a core component for implementing multiplayer features in Godot projects that require robust and reliable networking.
