Document: ENetMultiplayerPeer
Path: godot/classes/class_enetmultiplayerpeer.rst
Summary: Defines the methods available for managing ENet multiplayer connections, including creating servers and clients, and handling peer connections.

Method: add_mesh_peer(peer_id: int, host: ENetConnection) → Error
Adds a new peer to the mesh. Returns an Error code.

Method: create_client(address: String, port: int, channel_count: int = 0, in_bandwidth: int = 0, out_bandwidth: int = 0, local_port: int = 0) → Error
Creates a client connection to an ENet server. Returns an Error code.

Method: create_mesh(unique_id: int) → Error
Creates a new mesh network. Returns an Error code.

Method: create_server(port: int, max_clients: int = 32, max_channels: int = 0, in_bandwidth: int = 0, out_bandwidth: int = 0) → Error
Creates a new ENet server. Returns an Error code.

Method: get_peer(id: int) → ENetPacketPeer
Returns the ENetPacketPeer associated with the given peer ID. This method is callable only when the peer is connected.

Method: set_bind_ip(ip: String)
Sets the IP address to bind to when creating a server or connecting to a client. If not set, ENet will bind to all available addresses.
